						               													<description>&amp;quot;The animals in the forest are small and shy, they only play with an animal of the same age or their family. &amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Forestia is a card game of discarding from 3 years.&amp;#10;The first player to discard all his cards wins a token.&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to be the first to win the number of chips expected early in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     2 chips: for the youngest, and games with a large number of participants&amp;#10;     3 chips: for the most adventurous players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The duration of a game is less than 5 minutes, which corresponds to the concentration capacity of a 3-year-old child.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Forestia is a fun way to learn how to count and count from 1 to 3. It is an intellectually complex task for a child to count, not recite 1, 2, 3, 4, 5. This game allows you to play with the colors, then gently bring the child to count the candles on the cards to learn how to count while having fun. Then the first tactics with the first special card: the Joker card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Forestia is an evolving game with the addition of special cards as the child evolves. At 6 or 7 years old, the child can play with all the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: it is possible to play up to 12 players with 2 boxes of Forestia.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The ergonomics of the cards have been studied to allow to play with right-handers as left-handed. In addition each color is associated with only 1 symbol, which makes it easy to play with people with visual impairment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
